<task id="051" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate FilePreviewDialog to canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` wrapper</title>
    <phase>Wave 3 — SendEmailDialog + FilePreview</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>050</dependencies>
    <blocks>054</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, communication, refactoring, migration</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Removes inline `fetch` to `/api/communications/send` from a LegalWorkspace consumer (one of the core FR-14 success criteria); changes prop contract; must respect ADR-033 (canonical send-email pattern, MUST NOT inline fetch) + ADR-019 (typed error contract) + ADR-021 (Fluent UI v9). Touches `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` — production-shipped surface.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential gate: depends on 050 (canonical wrapper integration). Single file modification in `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`; running in parallel with 053 (consumer audit) risks divergent state on the same dependency chain.</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>FR-14</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Migrate `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx` to use the canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` wrapper from `@spaarke/ui-components`. Remove the inline `handleSendEmail` function and inline `fetch` call to `/api/communications/send`. Update consumer call sites within `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` to pass canonical props (`open` / `onClose` / `onSent` / `onError`) instead of the legacy `onSend` callback.

    Empirical state (CLAUDE.md row + spec FR-14): `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` currently has inline `handleSendEmail` + inline `fetch` to `/api/communications/send`. This is one of the 6 ad-hoc send-email implementations R3 is consolidating. After this task, the file MUST contain zero `fetch.*communications/send` references.

    Post-migration acceptance: the file's "Send by Email" path is now: user clicks the action → `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` toggles a state variable to open `<SendEmailDialog />` → wrapper owns the send (delegates to engine + `sendCommunication()`) → on success, wrapper calls `onSent` which `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` uses to dismiss the dialog + show a Fluent toast. On error, `onError` receives a `SendCommunicationError` which the parent displays.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer authoritative on LegalWorkspace consumer integration patterns. Familiar with the canonical wrapper contract per FR-03, the inline-fetch anti-pattern this migration replaces, and the `authenticatedFetch` injection pattern used by LegalWorkspace (provided by the host bootstrap).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx` mounts `<SendEmailDialog />` from `@spaarke/ui-components` for its "Send by Email" action. Inline `handleSendEmail` + inline `fetch` REMOVED. Canonical prop signature consumed. LegalWorkspace solution builds clean. Grep verification: zero `fetch.*communications/send` references in the file.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` is the LegalWorkspace file-preview surface (open a file → preview thumbnail + metadata → optional actions like "Send by Email"). The current implementation directly calls `fetch('/api/communications/send', ...)` with an inline request body construction — bypassing both the typed `sendCommunication()` wrapper AND the canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` UI. This is the most visible R3 fragmentation case in LegalWorkspace.

      The migration is straightforward because LegalWorkspace already has `authenticatedFetch` available (provided by the solution's auth bootstrap) and the canonical wrapper accepts it via props. The wrapper handles dialog open/close state, attachment carrying (the previewed file as a `wizard`-source attachment), and error surfacing.

      The current `ISendEmailDialogProps` (pre-R3) had a legacy `onSend` callback the parent populated with the request body. The canonical signature drops `onSend` entirely — the wrapper sends, the parent reacts to `onSent` / `onError`. This is the breaking shape change called out in FR-14.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx (PRIMARY — migration target)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/ (audit for any sibling files referencing `handleSendEmail`)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx (canonical wrapper produced by task 050)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts (`sendCommunication()` + `SendCommunicationError`)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/package.json (verify `@spaarke/ui-components` dependency)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">MUST NOT inline `fetch` to `/api/communications/send`. MUST use canonical wrapper.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Error path consumes `SendCommunicationError` typed class via `onError` callback; no string-only error handling.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Replacement dialog chrome is Fluent UI v9 (from the canonical wrapper); LegalWorkspace toast notifications on success/error also Fluent v9.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">No direct `@spaarke/auth` import added; LegalWorkspace's existing host bootstrap provides `authenticatedFetch` which is threaded through wrapper props.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-14">Post-migration: zero `fetch.*communications/send` references in `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-25">No new LegalWorkspace fork created during this migration — only consume from `@spaarke/ui-components`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="repo">LegalWorkspace solution build MUST remain green.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
