  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx` in full. Identify: the inline `handleSendEmail` function, the inline `fetch('/api/communications/send', ...)` call, the current `<SendEmailDialog />` mount call site (if present) using legacy `onSend`, the imports.</step>
    <step order="2">Grep `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/` for any sibling files that reference `handleSendEmail` or share request-body construction.</step>
    <step order="3">Sketch the migration in task notes: list which lines/blocks get deleted (inline fetch, inline handler) vs preserved (open-state toggle, attachment source plumbing).</step>
    <step order="4">Replace the inline send logic with the canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` mount: pass `open`, `onClose`, `initialTo` (if `FilePreviewDialog` had a `defaultRecipient`), `attachmentSources` (configure for the previewed file as a single `wizard`-source or `local`-source attachment with the file already loaded), `onSent`, `onError`. Remove `handleSendEmail`.</step>
    <step order="5">Update the parent's `onSent` handler to dismiss the email dialog + show a Fluent toast "Email sent". Update `onError` to display a Fluent error banner with `error.detail` and `error.correlationId`.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify the previewed file is carried as an attachment by the wrapper — confirm with the FilePreview's existing file-buffer access pattern. If the file lives in SPE, configure `attachmentSources={['spe']}` with the SPE driveItem ID pre-selected; if it's loaded into memory, configure `attachmentSources={['local']}` with the blob/File pre-attached.</step>
    <step order="7">Update imports: add `SendEmailDialog` from `@spaarke/ui-components`, remove now-unused imports (e.g., direct `fetch` helpers, request-body type defs that were inline).</step>
    <step order="8">Grep verify: `fetch.*communications/send` returns zero hits in `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `npm run build` in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` (use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` if dependencies are stale, per CLAUDE.md §11). Verify clean.</step>
    <step order="10">Run `npm run lint`. Verify clean.</step>
    <step order="11">Quality gate (Step 9.5 per FULL rigor): invoke `/code-review` on the modified `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`. Invoke `/adr-check` to verify no ADR-033 / ADR-019 / ADR-021 violations.</step>
    <step order="12">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 051 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="13">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed, advance to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

